modules.description: Tracks network packet statistics with counters for received and transmitted packets. Provides functions to record packet sizes and reset counters. Used to monitor traffic volume and packet counts in MirageOS network devices.

This module provides functions for connecting to and transmitting data over network devices, including sending packets and handling disconnections. It operates on network device descriptors and packet data structures. Concrete use cases include sending Ethernet frames and managing packet transmission errors like invalid lengths or disconnected devices.

This module handles network device operations, providing functions to send packets, manage connections, and report transmission errors. It works with network device descriptors and packet data structures, offering concrete functionality for tasks like sending Ethernet frames and handling packet size validation. The Stats submodule tracks and updates packet statistics, such as received and transmitted byte and packet counts, enabling traffic monitoring for MirageOS network devices.
